CompiledQuery Class

In this Article

Provides for compilation and caching of queries for reuse.

Syntax

Declaration

public sealed class CompiledQuery

Inheritance Hierarchy

Remarks

Conceptually this class contains a single method (Compile) with several overloads. You call the <xref:System.Data.Linq.CompiledQuery.Compile%2A> method to create a new delegate to represent the compiled query.

Note

Compilation does not occur until the first time the query is executed.

Returns the query as a lambda expression.
